# Storefront Preview

## Purpose
Simulates a J.Crew e-commerce storefront. Approved products appear as cards; hovering over a product image crossfades to an auto-playing video.

## ProductCard Component
- Props: `Product` (id, title, price, primaryImageUrl, videoUrl)
- Default state: static product image
- On `mouseenter`: preload and play the video, crossfade opacity to show video over image
- On `mouseleave`: pause video, fade back to static image
- Below the image: product title, price, and "Add to Cart" button (non-functional, for demo)

## Data Flow
- `preview/page.tsx` reads `Product[]` from localStorage on mount
- If no products saved, shows an empty state with link back to generator
- Products are added to localStorage when the user approves a generated video in the main workflow

## Styling
- CSS Grid: 4 columns on desktop, 2 on mobile
- Aspect ratio `3:4` for product images (portrait, J.Crew style)
- Minimal hover effects — the video IS the hover effect
